Christmas Planner Guide

How to organise, save, and enjoy the festive planners in this folder without losing your sparkle.

Quick Start

  1. Keep the folder together. The planners use the shared logo in ../files; move the entire christmas-planners folder if you reorganise.
  2. Open in your browser. Double-click any HTML file (Safari, Chrome, Edge, or Firefox all work). Everything loads instantly.
  3. Type right into the page. Update details as plans evolve; no spreadsheets or extra apps required.
  4. On mobile: The planners work in a phone browser, though text boxes may appear smaller while remaining editable.

Entries save automatically to your browsers local storage. Reopen the same planner in the same browser and your notes will still be there throughout the season.

Save, Print, or Reset

  • Auto-save: Theres no save button: changes are captured as you type.
  • Print/PDF: Use the Print / Save as PDF button near the top of each planner when you want a hard copy or to share a snapshot.
  • Clear entries: Select Clear saved entries for a fresh start on just that planner.
  • Switching devices: Copy anything important before moving to another computer or browser. Local storage does not sync automatically.
  • Archive versions: Duplicate the folder (e.g., christmas-planners-2024) if you want to keep an annual record.

Planner Overviews

Tap any planner name below to open the live, auto-saving version in this browser.

christmas-budget-planner.html

Track gifts, food, experiences, and your overall budget ceiling with live totals.

christmas-party-planner.html

Organise invitations, menu, dcor, and a run of show so the celebration stays on course.

christmas-countdown-calendar.html

Plan daily highlights for 1-25 December, including support notes and completion checkboxes.

boxing-day-reset.html

Process the holiday rush with guided prompts for closure, energy reset, space reset, and a bridge to the new year.

gratitude-memory-journal.html

Capture the people, senses, and stories that made this season special, plus a note to future you.

handmade-gift-tracker.html

Manage craft projects with supply lists, timelines, packaging plans, and reflection prompts.

christmas-shopping-list.html

Track gifts, food, drinks, and miscellaneous buys with running totals so you stay on budget.

Tips

  • Bookmark the planners so your festive planning hub is always one click away.
  • Pair the countdown calendar with reminders on your phone so you never miss a joyful moment.
  • Use the budget totals to decide when to pause spending or shift funds between categories.
  • Need extra support? Add a duplicate planner for Boxing Day, New Years, or a separate Friendsmas gathering.
